        "pertanyaan": "<p>Bekantan, also known as the proboscis monkey, is a unique primate native to the island of Borneo. It is easily recognizable due to its large, distinctive nose, especially pronounced in males. Bekantans primarily inhabit mangrove forests, swamps, and coastal areas. They are excellent swimmers and are often seen leaping from tree to tree or diving into the water. Bekantans are herbivores, feeding mainly on leaves, fruits, and seeds. Their population is declining due to habitat loss and hunting. Conservation efforts are important to protect this species.<\/p><p>Which region is the natural habitat of bekantans?<\/p>",
